  instantiated on the server. The fix involved marking the
  component as a client component, as it was directly rendering ,
  which uses client-side hooks.
overview: The user wanted to add a "Surprise me" button to the application. This
  button, when clicked, would navigate to a random blog post. The implementation
  involved modifying the  component to include the button, a
  click handler, and the  hook for navigation. However, a runtime
  error occurred because  was being instantiated on the server side,
  even though  was marked as a client component. The root cause
  was that , which imports and renders , was a
  server component. The fix involved adding  to ,
  ensuring that both  and  are rendered on the
  client side, thus resolving the  instantiation error.
